Building CMS:
  1. install java, ant, tomcat5.5
  2. in fabric dir run ant jars
  3. in cms dir switch to fabricized version (cvs up -rPd cms_fabric
  4. in cms dir run ant

Configuring Tomcat:
  5. link fab jars into web dir    (ln -s lib/fabric{,-rt}.jar tests/cms/web/WEB-INF/lib/
  6. link web into webapps dir     (sudo ln -s tests/cms/web /var/lib/tomcat5.5/webapps
  7. link 55cms.policy into tomcat (sudo ln -s tests/cms/config/55cms.policy /etc/tomcat5.5/policy.d
  8. tell tomcat where fabric is   (sudo echo "fabric.prefix=`pwd`" >> /etc/tomcat5.5/catalina.properties 
  9. if your store is not fabric-cms.systems.cs.cornell.edu edit web/WEB-INF/web.xml accordingly

Running CMS:
 10. restart tomcat                 (sudo service tomcat5.5 restart
 11. start the core                 (bin/fab-core --core fabric-cms.systems.cs.cornell.edu etc/keys/fabric-cms.systems.cs.cornell.edu.keystore etc/keys/trust.keystore password
 12. create the cmsserver principal (bin/fab --name cmsserver --make-principal fabric-cms.systems.cs.cornell.edu
 13. navigate to http://localhost:8180/web
